HEADWORD: Disposure
<hw>Dis*po"sure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Dispose</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of disposing; power to
dispose of; disposal; direction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give up⟦br⟧
My estate to his <qex>disposure</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposition; arrangement; position; posture.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In a kind of warlike <qex>disposure</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir H.
Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dispraisable</ent>⟦br⟧
